Attribute Value Templates


				DISelect extends the host language by allowing any
				attribute value to be specified as an Attribute Value
				Template (AVT). An AVT is an XPath expression which is
				evaluated to yield the value to be used for the
				attribute. To distinguish the use of an AVT as the value
				of an attribute, the expression is enclosed within curly
				braces {}.



				An AVT used within the source infoset can contain any
				XPath expression supported by the DISelect processor.
				During processing, the expression is evaluated and the
				result is used as the value of the attribute.






